                <![CDATA[In this module, practice your <b>selling skills</b> so you can apply them on the job.]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb1" order="21" trans="slideRight">
                <![CDATA[Read the following scenario of a conversation between a Parts Advisor and a phone customer who is interested in brakes for his Jeep. Prepare to answer questions on how you would follow the Customer-Driven Parts Sales Process to close the sale.]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb2" order="22">
                <![CDATA[<b>Parts Advisor:</b> <i>“Hello, this is Pete in the Hometown Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram Parts Department. How may I help you?”</i>]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb3" order="26">
                <![CDATA[<b>Customer:</b> <i>“Hi. I’m calling to find out if you have the parts for front brakes on a Jeep Patriot.”</i>]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb4" order="27">
                <![CDATA[<b>Parts Advisor:</b> <i>“I need a little more information to answer your question. Do you have the vehicle identification number for your Jeep?”</i>]]>
</bodyBullet>
              <bodyBullet id="bb5" order="28">
                <![CDATA[<b>Parts Advisor:</b> <i>“Whoa! Hold on a minute. I’ll be right back.”</i>]]>
</bodyBullet>
